cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CR 

The paper discusses a new index for quantifying an author's share in the impact of their published papers. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), computational complexity (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses on bibliometric analysis and citation metrics, we believe that cs.DL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR, and cs.CR.
